<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-000-660  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 000 660.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 31 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Macintosh accesses up to 14 megs with Virtual 2.0. (megabytes)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Woods, Wendy.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (programming)Virtual 2.0 (Computer program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersProduct IntroductionSoftware PackagesMemory.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MACINTOSH ACCESSES UP TO 14 MEGS WITH VIRTUAL 2.0 MENLO PARK, CALIFORNIA,U.S.A., 1989 OCT 27 (NB) -- A new software product promises to eliminate theeight megabyte memory barrier common to the best Macintoshes.andM;Virtual 2.0, the second generation of this product, allows an SE/30, IIx,IIcx, and IIci (all 68020 and 68030-based Macintoshes) to access not onlyeight megabytes of existing memory in such machines, but also the sixmegabytes of memory normally reserved for expansion cards.andP;  It allows the Macto use a portion of the hard disk drive as if it were RAM or random accessmemory.andP;  Once the Virtual software is installed, the Macintosh rapidlyaccesses the disk drive and operates as though it had up to 14 megabytes ofRAM installed.andM;Because Virtual behaves like ordinary RAM, users can employ such memory hogsas Multifinder and run several applications at once in windows on screen.andO;Currently, System 6.03, Apple's system software, only allows a Macintosh toaccess actual RAM, not &quot;virtual&quot; RAM but that is expected to be differentwith the release of System Software 7.0 next spring.andM;The product also allows memory size to be adjusted through a control paneldevice, and offers a disk defragmentation utility that provides contiguousclear space for the Virtual file.andM;Virtual 2.0, at $199, is sold in North America by Ingram Micro D andMacAmerica.andP;  It is also sold through distributors Softmart International inFrance, Prisma in Germany, Computers Unlimited in the UK, Program Paketet inSweden, Performance Sales in Australia and New Zealand, and SoftCode inCanada.andP;  In Switzerland the product is available through Systrade and in theNetherlands through ITF.andM;Newsbytes News Service will be doing a review of the product shortly.andM;(Wendy Woods/19891027/Press Contact: 415-324-0727)</TEXT></DOC>